Adjust rack to top position (top and bottom positions for 4 servings) and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Cut @Yukon Gold Potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch-thick wedges. Trim @Green Beans{6%ounce} if necessary. Halve, peel, and mince @Shallot{1} until you have 2 TBSP. Place @Black Peppercorns{1%tablespoon} in a #zip-close bag{}; crush with a #rolling pin{} or a heavy-bottomed pan. Mince @Chives{¼%ounce}.

Toss potatoes on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @Cooking Oil{4%teaspoon} and a big pinch of @Salt{} and @Pepper{}.

Roast on top rack until lightly browned, ~{10%minutes} (you'll add the green beans then).

Once potatoes have roasted, carefully push to one side of baking sheet.

Toss green beans on empty side with a drizzle of oil and a pinch of salt and pepper.

> For 4 servings, leave potatoes roasting and add green beans to a second sheet; roast on bottom rack.

Return to top rack until veggies are browned and tender, ~{10-15%minutes} more.

While veggies roast, pat @Chicken Cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; season all over with @Salt{} and @Pepper{}.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #medium pan{} (use a #large pan{} for 4 servings) over medium-high heat. Add chicken and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes} per side.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{} and set aside. Wash out pan.

Melt 1 TBSP @Butter{2%tablespoon} in same pan over medium heat. Add minced shallot and cook, stirring, until slightly softened, ~{1%minute}.

Add @Chicken Demi-Glace{1}, ¼ cup water (1⁄3 cup for 4 servings), and ½ tsp crushed peppercorns (1 tsp for 4). (Be sure to measure peppercorns.) Simmer until slightly thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Turn off heat. Stir in another 1 TBSP butter (2 TBSP for 4) and half the chives. Season with salt and more peppercorns if desired.

Thinly slice chicken crosswise.

Divide potatoes, green beans, and chicken between plates. Top chicken with sauce. Sprinkle with remaining chives and serve.